[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing run of the `cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer` triggered an AddressSanitizer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreport indicating a one-byte stack-buffer-overflow in `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcmspack.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, called via a chain through `CachedXFORM`, `cmsDoTransform`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`CreateNamedColorDevicelink`, and `cmsTransform2DeviceLink`. An attempted patch [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjusted the computation of pixel size in `cmsxform.c` to multiply component count [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby bytes per component, and changed the loop index in `cmsvirt.c` from a [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`int` to a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit `cmsUInt16Number`. After applying the patch, the same [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow persisted at a slightly different stack offset, showing that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow location in `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` was unchanged.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- An AddressSanitizer failure during fuzzing reports a stack-buffer-overflow in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes` at cmspack.[0m[1;92mc:130:13[0m[39m, reading one byte past a local buffer.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is triggered when `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` allocates several local [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects on its stack frame [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding an integer index, flags, and frame buffers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand then calls through to `UnrollChunkyBytes`, which reads beyond its intended [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer boundary.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer backtrace shows the sequence:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer.c  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` in cmsvirt.c  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` → `cmsDoTransform` → `CachedXFORM` → [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/cmsxform.c`, the `PixelSize` function was changed to compute “bytes per [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpixel” by multiplying the per-component byte count [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mT_BYTES[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m by the total[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumber of components [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mT_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mT_EXTRA[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and to return a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscaled size for double-precision formats.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/cmsvirt.c`, inside `cmsTransform2DeviceLink`, the loop index `i` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39moriginally a [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit int passed to `cmsDoTransform`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was replaced by a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsUInt16Number idx16` with the intention of matching expected input size for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdownstream code.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A subsequent fuzzing run produced an identical AddressSanitizer [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow, now pointing at offset [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m in the stack frame of [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsTransform2DeviceLink` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmspack.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The local variable reporting the overflow is now `idx16.i` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instead of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe original `i` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the overflow still overflows that variable’s stack [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslot, indicating that the underlying buffer size or access logic in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes` remains mismatched to the data provided.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmspack.c: around line [0m[1;36m130[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: verify [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer allocations and boundary checks versus the number of bytes read.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack layout in `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsvirt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: examine all local [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marrays/variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`i`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`idx16`, `dwFlags`, `FrmIn`, `FrmOut`, `LUT`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtheir sizes match the data passed to transformation routines.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The calculation of pixel and component sizes in `PixelSize` and elsewhere in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsxform.c`, ensuring consistent use of component counts, byte sizes, and [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The AddressSanitizer crash in UnrollChunkyBytes is caused by two mis-behaviors[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhenever a “chunky” pixel format carries multi-byte samples [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit per index [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min NamedColorIndex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m UnrollChunkyBytes always reads exactly one byte per channel [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*accum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` + `accum++`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, even when samples are two [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor more[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m bytes [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwide, so it drifts through its input buffer one byte at a time rather than one [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msample at a time.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Although UnrollChunkyBytes is passed a `Stride` argument [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe total bytes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto advance per pixel, i.e. BytesPerPlaneIn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it never uses it. Instead it simply [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns the pointer advanced by `nChan` bytes. For multi-byte samples this [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder-advances, so successive pixels overlap and eventually run off the bottom of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe local input buffer, clobbering adjacent stack variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`i.i`, `dwFlags`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39metc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Principles to Preserve  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not alter fuzz harnesses or test code.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintain existing pipeline logic: UnrollChunkyBytes remains the “FromInput” [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutine for chunky formats.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep PixelSize changes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes per component × component count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStride→BytesPerPlaneIn accurately reflects bytes per pixel.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure no regression for strictly [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit per channel formats.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Outline for cmspack.c  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `[0m[1;35mUnrollChunkyBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…, cmsUInt8Number* accum, cmsUInt32Number Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m At the top, save the initial pointer:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        cmsUInt8Number* start = accum;  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Compute the per-component byte‐width:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        cmsUInt32Number nChan = …  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing loop bound  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        cmsUInt32Number unit = Stride [0m[35m/[0m[39m nChan;  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In the loop over channels, replace  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        v = [0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*accum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        …  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        accum++;  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      with something like:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39munit == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            v = [0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*accum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39munit == [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            cmsUInt16Number raw = [0m[1;39m([0m[39maccum[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m << [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m | accum[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            v = Reverse ? [0m[1;35mREVERSE_FLAVOR_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39mraw[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : raw;  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m unlikely: but guard against divide-by-zero or >[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            v = [0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*accum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        …  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        accum += unit;  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m After the channel loop, return `start + Stride` instead of the old pointer.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Benefits and Correctness  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By computing `unit = Stride/nChan`, we automatically support [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte, [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mand in principle larger[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m samples.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The pointer returned now jumps exactly `Stride` bytes, correctly aligning to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe next pixel.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents reading past the local `wIn` buffer and keeps input reads within[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe pixel buffer.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit formats [0m[1;39m([0m[33munit[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fall back to the existing code path [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The modified loop index type in `cmsvirt.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `cmsUInt16Number idx16`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain, as it only shrinks the stack slot but no longer gets overrun.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side-Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other functions use UnrollChunkyBytes, so narrowing its scope here is safe.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PixelSize in cmsxform.c must remain as patched [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes/component × components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso that Stride is accurate.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new public API or tests are touched; existing coverage of [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit and planar [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformats continues to pass.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run all unit tests and both fuzzers:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • The cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer should no longer report a [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow in cmspack.c.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • Other transformation fuzzers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. cms_iccprofile_fuzzer, cmscms2_fuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould remain green.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a targeted unit test for a [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte chunky format [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. create a tiny [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m×[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX image[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to assert no over-read and correct transform [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
